Rating: 4
Huge hit with our family! Only advice is to only use 3 lbs. of potatoes. Would love to hear if anyone has ideas to lighten this up a bit.

Rating: 2
After reading the other reviews, I did cook the potatoes until they were done. I think it was a little too long because they became mushy and I wasn't able to get nice slices. After mixing the spices together as the recipe calls for I realized it was going to be a little to strong for my taste. I only used about a 1/4 TBS of the spice mixture on each layer...and it was just enough. I couldn't imagine using all that the recipe called for. I would use less cumin next time as it was the most overwhelming of the flavors to come through. I served it room temperature as the directions call to do, but ended up reheating it as it did not taste great at room temperature. Definately serve this after it cools for about 10 mins. I cooled it on a baking rack with a piece of foil under it because it was dripping oil from the cheese and sour cream. Overall, I enjoyed it, but some of my guests didn't care for the Indian flavors.

Rating: 4
Every time I make this it is a hit. It is quite rich so unless there are quite a few people it doesn't always get finished in one setting. I sometimes bring this for the holidays instead of making the marshmallow or sweet yam/sweet potato dish. I also always use the Maharaja curry powder from Penzy's. I highly recommend Penzy's spice company to everyone. The spices really are an important piece to this dish. Use quality spices and you will taste the difference.

Rating: 4
I had the good fortune to have this served to me at a friend's house last Thanksgiving. It was one of the best things I've ever had. The flavors were perfect.

Rating: 4
This recipe is excellent. I used the Maharaja curry powder from Penzy's Spice company. The key is to use really good quality cheese and spices. And not to skimp on the cheese. I used red skinned yams, the flavor is much much better than sweet potatoes as sweet potatoes don't fit with these spices very well, in my opinion at least. I also added lemon zest which gives it a nice dimension. I made this for a party and everyone loved it.

Rating: 1
This recipe, made exactly as directed, results in a beautiful dish with an enticing aroma. However, the flavors didn't blend well and the cheese (an excellent one) overpowered the flavor of the potatoes. I'm glad I tried it before deciding to serve it to guests. Disappointing.

